transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I put in an order just a few minutes ago, but I want to add express shipping, the one-day shipping.

Speaker 1: Okay. Yeah, I can definitely do that for you. I'm sure you understand, but this will go out tomorrow to arrive on Thursday.

Speaker 2: Okay, as long as I get it Thursday?

Speaker 1: Yeah, because it's just too late in the day for it to ship today, so it would ship tomorrow morning.

Speaker 2: Okay. But I can add that for you if you still want to do that.

Speaker 1: Yeah. Okay, just need your name and zip code, sir.

Speaker 2: Joe Glusak, G-L-U-S-A-K. You mean where it's getting delivered to?

Speaker 1: Either zip code will work. If you have a different billing, either one works.

Speaker 2: Let's see.

Speaker 1: It's got my – the shipping information is 46368.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Joe Glusak.

Speaker 2: Thanks, Joe. One second.

Speaker 1: Yep, 6625 Daniel Burnham Drive, Suite D.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay, and I'm good to charge $38 with the card on file?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that'll get it there Thursday, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that'll be the next day option.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay. Just so you know, for the future, I understand when you can go online and order is the time you can.

Speaker 2: But the cutoff is at 1 p.m. Eastern time to get it out that same day.

Speaker 1: Okay. Okay.

Speaker 2: But we're all set now.

Speaker 1: All right. Thanks a lot.

Speaker 2: Thanks, Joe. Have a good one.

Speaker 1: All right. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
